<h1>Hanz Geeratz</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://dharma-mirror.com/now/">dharma-mirror.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Hamburg

Germany
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I work as CTO and Scrum master @ Speicher 210 <<a href="http://www.sp210.com>">http://www.sp210.com></a> of which I am also the co-founder.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I am a No Meat Athlete, Ultra-runner, Scrum master, Coffee drinker and part time Buddhist.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I run a lot and I run long distances, and this on a plant based diet. For me running is a way of meditation and part of a non-theistic spirituality, like Mindfulness meditation techniques. I consider myself a Buddhist without believes, part-time Buddhist. Next to that I am CTO and co-founder of a software development company.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
“No one can build you the bridge on which you, and only you, must cross the river of life,” “There may be countless trails and bridges and demigods who would gladly carry you across; but only at the price of pawning and forgoing yourself.” – Nietzsche
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“Buddha's Brain: The Practical Neuroscience of Happiness” by Rick Hanson
</p>

